  "lang": "ja",
  "description": "The 46 basic katakana (used for loanwords). Each kana is tested both ways (symbol→reading and reading→symbol), tracked separately.",
  "primerTitle": "Reading katakana",
  "primer": "**Katakana** is the second Japanese phonetic script — same 46 sounds as hiragana, but a different set of angular shapes. It is used mainly for **loanwords** (コーヒー *kōhī* = coffee), foreign names, onomatopoeia, and emphasis. The sounds follow the same **gojūon** order: five vowels, then each consonant row.\n\n| | a | i | u | e | o |\n|---|---|---|---|---|---|\n| **–** | ア a | イ i | ウ u | エ e | オ o |\n| **k** | カ ka | キ ki | ク ku | ケ ke | コ ko |\n| **s** | サ sa | シ **shi** | ス su | セ se | ソ so |\n| **t** | タ ta | チ **chi** | ツ **tsu** | テ te | ト to |\n| **n** | ナ na | ニ ni | ヌ nu | ネ ne | ノ no |\n| **h** | ハ ha | ヒ hi | フ **fu** | ヘ he | ホ ho |\n| **m** | マ ma | ミ mi | ム mu | メ me | モ mo |\n| **y** | ヤ ya | | ユ yu | | ヨ yo |\n| **r** | ラ ra | リ ri | ル ru | レ re | ロ ro |\n| **w** | ワ wa | | | | ヲ **wo** |\n| **n** | ン **n** | | | | |\n\n**Irregular readings** (same four as hiragana): シ = *shi*, チ = *chi*, ツ = *tsu*, フ = *fu*.\n\n**Easily-confused look-alikes** — these trip up almost everyone:\n- **シ (shi)** vs **ツ (tsu)**: シ strokes sweep up and are flatter; ツ strokes come down and are more vertical.\n- **ソ (so)** vs **ン (n)**: ソ is more vertical; ン sweeps up and is flatter.\n- **ヘ (he)** is the *same glyph* as hiragana へ.\n\n**Special kana:** **ン** is the standalone *n*; **ヲ** (*wo*) is the object particle and is rare in katakana. The y- and w-rows have the same gaps as hiragana.",
